Here are self care tips you should consider doing from time to time this year!

1. Go for walking. Last week, we talked about nature walks and how it benefits not just our physical body but also improves our mental health.

2. Have a bubble bath - Baths are full of relaxation and give you the privacy you need to give yourself a mental, emotional, and spiritual.

3. Catch up with a loved one! Call or text them or maybe take them out for dinner and just spend a lil moment with them.

4. Meditate - Meditation reduces stress and anxiety, improves emotional health, enhances self awareness, improves sleep, and can even help you generate more kindness. So try meditation out today! Your mind will feel peace and your body will thank you for the extra time you spent on it!

5. Lastly, you deserve to eat your favorite food. Treat yourself!

How to prevent let down from happening - this is for everyone, including me.

1. Don't commit to things you cant do or are not willing to do.

2. Set boundaries for yourself so you don’t let anyone down.

3. Be clear on the objective & the request so you can make sure to deliver & know all the details before committing to more than you realized.

4. Make it a priority and schedule it.

5. Ask for guidance if needed.

Gaby Aghion (1921–2014) was born in Alexandria, Egypt, to a Greek Jewish father and a mother of Italian Jewish descent. From an early age, the family moved in cultured and politically progressive circles. In 1940 she married her childhood friend Raymond Aghion, son of an eminent Egyptian Jewish banking family. In 1945, as World War II ended, the couple moved to Paris, where their life orbited around the Saint-Germain-des-Prés district. There they found a circle of friends among the Surrealist artists and intellectuals of the Left Bank.

In 1952, Gaby founded her own fashion label, which she named Chloé because she liked the feminine roundness of its letters. Her hope was to liberate women from the many constraints of couture design by creating stylish everyday garments she and women like her would want to wear. To found her own label was a remarkable achievement for a woman in postwar France.

At Chloé she established a lasting tradition of hiring emerging designers. “I have no talent. I recognize the talent in others,” she once remarked, preferring to remain outside the spotlight and instead to advance the work of the designers she championed as a creative entrepreneur.

Learn more about Aghion's daring vision and prolific legacy in "Mood of the moment: Gaby Aghion and the house of Chloé" on view now at the Jewish Museum. Plan your visit Plan your visit: https://thejm.net/3fA1y2m.

🌞🌿 Vitamin D: The Sunshine Vitamin! 🌞🌿

Are you getting enough Vitamin D? This essential nutrient is often called the "Sunshine Vitamin" because your skin produces it when exposed to sunlight. Here are some fantastic benefits and tips to ensure you're getting your daily dose:

Benefits of Vitamin D:
✨ Supports strong bones and teeth.
✨ Boosts immune function.
✨ Improves mood and fights depression.
✨ Regulates insulin levels.
✨ Enhances cardiovascular health.

Tips to Get Enough Vitamin D:
1️⃣ Spend some time in the sun: Aim for 10-30 minutes of sunlight exposure on your skin a few times a week.
2️⃣ Eat Vitamin D-rich foods: Fatty fish, egg yolks, and fortified dairy products are excellent sources.
3️⃣ Consider supplements: If you have limited sun exposure or dietary restrictions, supplements can help fill the gap.
4️⃣ Get your levels checked: A blood test can determine if you have a deficiency and guide your supplementation.

Remember, maintaining optimal Vitamin D levels contributes to overall well-being. So, soak up some sun responsibly and nourish your body with this essential nutrient! 🌞💪😊
